Indicator: Years of Life Lost Before Age 75
dataSource: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
description: Years of Potential Life Lost Before Age 75 (YPLL-75) is an age-adjusted rate per 100,000 of the population. It is based on the average years a person would have lived if he or she had not died before age 75.
Note: The methods for calculating Years of Life Lost Before Age 75, previously called Premature Death, have been updated since prior reports.

Indicator: Life Expectancy in Years, Male
dataSource: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
description: Life expectancy at birth is the expected number of years to be lived by someone born at the time of calculation, if mortality at each age remains constant in the future.
Note: Caution low sample size: Upper Northwest, Upper North, Lower Northeast, Central Northeast, North Delaware, River Wards, Lower North, Central, West, University/Southwest. Omitted due to insufficient sample size: Lower Northwest, West Park, Lower Southwest.

Indicator: Life Expectancy in Years, Female
dataSource: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
description: Life expectancy at birth is the expected number of years to be lived by someone born at the time of calculation, if mortality at each age remains constant in the future.
Note: Caution low sample size: Upper Far Northeast, Lower Far Northeast, Central Northeast, North Delaware, Lower Northeast, Upper Northwest, Lower Northwest, River Wards, Lower North, Central, University/Southwest. Omitted due to insufficient sample size: West Park, Lower Southwest.

Indicator: Poor or Fair Health
dataSource: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
description: Percentage of adults who rate their health as "fair" or "poor" in response to the question, "In general, would you say that your health is excellent, very good, good, fair, or poor?"
Note: Two years of Household Health Survey data (2012 and 2014/15) were combined to provide more reliable estimates by planning district, therefore these numbers are not directly comparable with previous estimates. Caution low sample size: West Park, Lower Southwest.

Indicator: Adult smoking Prevalence
dataSource: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
description: Percentage of adults who have smoked at least 100 cigarettes in their lifetime and currently smoke "every day" or "some days."
Note: Two years of Household Health Survey data (2012 and 2014/15) were combined to provide more reliable estimates by planning district, therefore these numbers are not directly comparable with previous estimates. Caution low sample size: River Wards, West Park, Lower Southwest.

Indicator: Adult Obesity Prevalence
dataSource: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
description: Percentage of adults with BMI greater than or equal to 30kg/m2, based on self-reported height and weight.
Note: Two years of Household Health Survey data (2012 and 2014/15) were combined to provide more reliable estimates by planning district, therefore these numbers are not directly comparable with previous estimates. Caution low sample size: West Park, Lower Southwest.

Indicator: Adults Drinking ≥1 Sugary Drink Daily
dataSource: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
description: Percentage of adults who drank soda, sweetened fruit drinks, and/or bottled teas at least once a day for past 30 days. Respondents were instructed “do not include diet soda/drinks.”
Note: Examples provided to respondents included Coke, 7-Up, Snapple, Hugs, lemonade, and Kool-Aid. Caution low sample size: River Wards, West Park, Lower Southwest.

Indicator: Adult Hypertension Prevalence
dataSource: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
description: Percentage of adults who have been told by a doctor or other health professional that they have high blood pressure or hypertension. Excludes respondents with a history of gestational hypertension only.
Note: Two years of Household Health Survey data (2012 and 2014/15) were combined to provide more reliable estimates by planning district, therefore these numbers are not directly comparable with previous estimates. Caution low sample size: Lower Southwest. Omitted due to insufficient sample size: West Park.

Indicator: Adult Diabetes Prevalence
dataSource: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
description: Percentage of adults who have been told by a doctor or other health professional that they have or have had diabetes. Excludes respondents with a history of gestational diabetes only.
Note: Two years of Household Health Survey data (2012 and 2014/15) were combined to provide more reliable estimates by planning district, therefore these numbers are not directly comparable with previous estimates.

Indicator: New HIV Diagnoses per 100,000 People
dataSource: HIV Surveillance Data, AIDS Activities Coordinating Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Rate of new HIV diagnoses per 100,000 population.
Note: Omitted due to insufficient sample size: Lower Far Northeast, Lower Northwest.

Indicator: New HIV Diagnoses From Male-to-Male Sexual Contact
dataSource: HIV Surveillance Data, AIDS Activities Coordinating Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Percentage of new HIV diagnoses from male-to-male sexual contact.
Note: Omitted due to insufficient sample size: Lower Far Northeast, Lower Northwest.

Indicator: New HIV Diagnoses From Heterosexual Contact
dataSource: HIV Surveillance Data, AIDS Activities Coordinating Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Percentage of new HIV diagnoses from heterosexual contact.
Note: Omitted due to insufficient sample size: Lower Far Northeast, Lower Northwest.

Indicator: New HIV Diagnoses From Injection Drug Use
dataSource: HIV Surveillance Data, AIDS Activities Coordinating Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Percentage of new HIV diagnoses from injection drug use.
Note: Omitted due to insufficient sample size: Lower Far Northeast, Lower Northwest.

Indicator: New HIV Diagnoses From "Other" Transmission Category
dataSource: HIV Surveillance Data, AIDS Activities Coordinating Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Percentage of new HIV diagnoses from "other" transmission category.
Note: Omitted due to insufficient sample size: Lower Far Northeast, Lower Northwest.

Indicator: Retention in HIV/AIDS Care
dataSource: HIV Surveillance Data, AIDS Activities Coordinating Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Percentage of persons living with diagnosed HIV having had 2 or more CD4 or viral load test results, at least 3 months apart, during a 12 month period.
Note: The data displayed for North Delaware includes persons who were diagnosed or received treatment in the Philadelphia Prison System. Inclusion of these individuals may artificially inflate HIV prevalence resulting in artificially lowered HIV retention rates.

Indicator: Viral Suppression
dataSource: HIV Surveillance Data, AIDS Activities Coordinating Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Percentage of persons diagnosed living with HIV, who were alive at year end and had a viral load < 200 at most recent test. Persons diagnosed living with HIV whose viral load was not assessed were considered unsuppressed.
Note: The data displayed for North Delaware includes persons who were diagnosed or received treatment in the Philadelphia Prison System. Inclusion of these individuals may artificially inflate HIV prevalence resulting in artificially lowered HIV viral suppression rates.

Indicator: Teen Chlamydia Rate per 100,000 Teens, 15-19 Years of Age
dataSource: Division of Disease Control, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Diagnosed chlamydia infection rate per 100,000 teens age 15-19 years.

Indicator: Teen Gonorrhea rate per 100,000 Teens, 15-19 Years of Age
dataSource: Division of Disease Control, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Diagnosed gonorrhea infection rate per 100,000 teens age 15-19 years.

Indicator: Low Birth Weight Births
dataSource: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
description: Percentage of live-born infants weighing less than 2,500 grams - or 5 pounds 8 ounces - at birth.
Note: The methods for calculating low birth weights have been updated since prior reports.

Indicator: Late or No Prenatal Care
dataSource: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
description: Percentage of women who received prenatal care either in the third trimester or not at all, out of all women for whom the timing of prenatal care is known.

Indicator: Breastfeeding Initiation
dataSource: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
description: Percentage of women initiating breastfeeding before hospital discharge, out of all women for whom breastfeeding status is known.
Note: The methods for calculating breastfeeding initiation have been updated since prior reports.

Indicator: Children Up to Date on Immunizations, 19-35 Months of Age
dataSource: Division of Disease Control, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Percentage of children, age 19-35 months, who have completed the recommended vaccination schedule 4:3:1:3 (DTaP : IPV : MMR : Hib).

Indicator: Newly Identified Elevated Blood Lead Levels (5-9 mcg/dL) in Children, < 6 Years of Age
dataSource: Pennsylvania's National Electronic Disease Surveillance System (PA-NEDSS), as reported by Environmental Health Services, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Percentage of children, 0-5 years old, with newly identified blood lead levels (BLLs) from 5-9 mcg/dL using any blood specimens for screening.

Indicator: Newly Identified Elevated Blood Lead Levels (10+ mcg/dL) in Children, < 6 Years of Age
dataSource: Pennsylvania's National Electronic Disease Surveillance System (PA-NEDSS), as reported by Environmental Health Services, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Percentage of children, 0-5 years old, with newly identified blood lead levels (BLLs) at or above 10 mcg/dL using any blood specimens for screening.

Indicator: Pedestrian and Bicycle Crashes per 100,000 Children, < 18 Years of Age
dataSource: Pennsylvania Department of Transportation
description: Rate of pedestrian and bicyclist crashes involving motor vehicles per 100,000 children under 18.

Indicator: Adults Without Insurance, 18-64 Years of Age
dataSource: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
description: Percentage of adults, age 18-64 years, reporting no source of insurance.
Note: Caution low sample size: Lower Far Northeast, Central Northeast, Lower Northeast, West, South, Lower Southwest. Omitted due to insufficient sample size: Lower Northwest, West Park, Lower North, University/Southwest.

Indicator: Adults Covered by Medicaid, 18-64 Years of Age
dataSource: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
description: Percentage of adults, age 18-64 years, reporting insurance coverage through Medicaid, Medical Assistance (M.A.), HealthChoices, or Access Card.
Note: Caution low sample size: Upper Northwest, Upper North, Lower Northeast, North, West, University/Southwest, South. Omitted due to insufficient sample size: Upper Far Northeast, River Wards, Lower North, West park, Lower Southwest.

Indicator: Adults Forgoing Care Due to Cost, 18-64 Years of Age
dataSource: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
description: Percentage of adults, age 18-64 years, answering "yes" to the question, "In the past year, has there been any time when you were sick or injured AND did not seek health care because of the cost?"
Note: Two years of Household Health Survey data (2012 and 2014/15) were combined to provide more reliable estimates by planning district, therefore these numbers are not directly comparable with previous estimates. Caution low sample size: River Wards. Omitted due to insufficient sample size: West Park.

Indicator: Girls Completing 3-Dose HPV Vaccine, 13-17 Years of Age
dataSource: Division of Disease Control, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Percentage of girls, age 13-17 years, who received 3 doses of HPV vaccine out of all girls 13-17 years in the population.
Note: Data are based on local reporting of immunizations provided by clinicians, and some underreporting for adolescents may occur.

Indicator: Food Establishments in Compliance with Food Safety Regulations Upon Initial Annual Inspection
dataSource: Environmental Health Services, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Percentage of food establishments in compliance with food safety regulations upon initial annual inspection by the Philadelphia Department of Public Health.
Note: Some establishments included in the overall compliance rate are not included in the planning district dimension due to non-permanent locations.

Indicator: Rat Complaints per 10,000 People
dataSource: Environmental Health Services, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Rate of rat complaint calls to the Philadelphia Department of Public Health per 10,000 residents.

Indicator: Philadelphia Building Construction and Occupancy Code Violations per 1,000 Occupied Housing Units
dataSource: City of Philadelphia Licenses and Inspections
description: Rate of Philadelphia Building Construction and Occupancy Code violations per 1,000 occupied housing units. Violations are based on follow-up inspections to complaints filed through Philly 311.

Indicator: Homicide Mortality Rate per 100,000 People
dataSource: Medical Examiner's Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Rate of homicide deaths per 100,000 persons.

Indicator: Firearm Homicide Rate per 100,000 People
dataSource: Medical Examiner's Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Rate of intentional deaths by discharge of firearm per 100,000 persons.

Indicator: Adults with Diagnosed Mental Health Condition
dataSource: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
description: Percentage of adults answering "yes" to the question, "Have you ever been diagnosed with any mental health condition, including clinical depression, anxiety disorder or bipolar disorder?"
Note: Two years of Household Health Survey data (2012 and 2014/15) were combined to provide more reliable estimates by planning district, therefore these numbers are not directly comparable with previous estimates. Omitted due to insufficient sample size: West Park.

Indicator: Opioid-Related Mortality Rate per 100,000 People
dataSource: Medical Examiner's Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Rate of deaths per 100,000 persons that were determined by the medical examiner to be caused by drug/medication overdose and for which a toxicology test was positive for an opioid.
Note: Opioids include heroin, morphine, methadone, and all prescriptions opioids such as codeine, hydrocodone, and oxycodone.

Indicator: Low-to-no Walkable Access to Healthy Foods and High Poverty
dataSource: Get Healthy Philly, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
description: Percentage of population living in high-poverty areas with low-to-no walkable access to healthy foods as assessed in PDPH's [Food Access Report](http://www.phila.gov/health/pdfs/WalkableAccessHealthyFood20122014.pdf).
Note: Please note that data definitions and sources differ across dimensions for this indicator.

Indicator: Access to Nearby Parks or Outdoor Space
dataSource: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
description: Percentage of adults responding yes to the question, “Is there a park or other outdoor space in your neighborhood that you’re comfortable visiting during the day?”
Note: Two years of Household Health Survey data (2012 and 2014/15) were combined to provide more reliable estimates by planning district, therefore these numbers are not directly comparable with previous estimates. Caution low sample size: Lower Southwest.

Indicator: Pedestrian and Bicycle Crashes per 100,000 People
dataSource: Pennsylvania Department of Transportation
description: Rate of pedestrian and bicyclist crashes involving motor vehicles per 100,000 persons.

Indicator: Adults Completing Some College, ≥ 25 Years of Age
dataSource: US Census Bureau, American Community Survey, 5-year estimates
description: Percentage of adults, 25 years or older, who completed at least some college.
Note: Please note that data years differ across dimensions for this indicator.

Indicator: Unemployment, ≥16 Years of Age
dataSource: US Census Bureau, American Community Survey, 5-year estimates
description: Percentage of population, 16 years or older, who are unemployed but seeking work.
Note: Please note that data sources and years differ across dimensions for this indicator.

Indicator: Philadelphians Living in Poverty
dataSource: US Census Bureau, American Community Survey, 5-year estimates
description: Percentage of population with an income below 100% of the federal poverty level (FPL).
Note: In 2014, the FPL was equivalent to a yearly income of no more than $11,670 for an individual, or $23,850 for a family of 4. Please note that data years differ across dimensions for this indicator.

Indicator: Children Living in Poverty, < 18 years of age
dataSource: US Census Bureau, American Community Survey, 5-year estimates
description: Percentage of children under 18 with a family income below 100% of the federal poverty level (FPL).
Note: In 2014, the FPL was equivalent to a yearly income of no more than $11,670 for an individual, or $23,850 for a family of 4. Please note that data years differ across dimensions for this indicator.

Indicator: Children in Single-Parent Households, < 18 Years of Age
dataSource: US Census Bureau, American Community Survey, 5-year estimates
description: Percentage of all children in family households that live in a household headed by a single parent (male or female head of household with no spouse present).

Indicator: Social Capital
dataSource: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
description: Percentage of adults reporting "yes" to, "Have people in your neighborhood ever worked together to improve the neighborhood? For example, through a neighborhood watch, creating a community garden, building a community playground, or participating in a block party."
Note: Caution low sample size: Upper Far Northeast, Lower Northwest, River Wards, Lower Southwest. Omitted due to insufficient sample size: West Park.
